# Prod-only Cloud Run env overrides for the webapi service (deploy/webapi/deploy.sh).
#
# Copy this file to `.env.prod` (same directory) and fill in the values below.
# `.env.prod` is git-ignored: it carries values that MUST reach the PRODUCTION
# service but deliberately do NOT live in the dev/worktree repo-root `.env`. At
# deploy time deploy.sh layers this file ON TOP of `.env` (same allowlist; the
# values here WIN), so a routine `make webapi-deploy` never drops them — no more
# out-of-band / image-only deploy just to preserve IAP_AUDIENCE.
#
# Only keys matching the deploy.sh allowlist are applied (anything else is ignored):
#   GCP_PROJECT_ID, BQ_LOCATION, CACHE_*, IAP_AUDIENCE, COMTRADE_BRAZIL_ISO,
#   ATTRIBUTE_EDITORS_ALLOWED_EMAILS, BQ_MAX_BYTES_BILLED, FEEDBACK_GITHUB_REPO
#
# NOTE: this is for non-secret identifiers/config ONLY. Real credentials (e.g. the
# feedback GitHub token) stay in Secret Manager and are mounted by deploy.sh —
# never put a token here.

# Cloud Run DIRECT IAP audience — arms the in-app IAP JWT verification
# (serving/iap.py), defense-in-depth on top of the platform IAP. Format for direct
# Cloud Run IAP is the service resource path:
#   /projects/<PROJECT_NUMBER>/locations/<REGION>/services/<SERVICE_NAME>
IAP_AUDIENCE=/projects/<PROJECT_NUMBER>/locations/<REGION>/services/<SERVICE_NAME>

# Feedback channel: the GitHub repo (owner/name) that "Reportar problema" forwards
# issues to. The token itself is the Secret Manager secret `feedback-github-token`,
# NOT set here.
FEEDBACK_GITHUB_REPO=<owner>/<repo>
